using linkchecker, i see current master links at 2863 and errors at 276:

```
That's it. 2863 links in 161 URLs checked. 0 warnings found. 276 errors found.
```

Adding the following MakeFile publish section is close:

```
publish:
    @hugo
    @pip install linkchecker
    @linkchecker public/index.html -F csv
    @cut -sd ';' -f 1,2 linkchecker-out.csv | tr ';' ' ' |awk '{ print $2 " " $1}' | sort -u
```

That's great that we can use pip install. No need to support windows/linux for now. Let's name the make target 'site' so it builds and verified the site locally. Publish is different, and we'll probably do that separately. I've committed an outline here:
https://github.com/twitter/heron/blob/master/website/Makefile#L17

So we have something like this:

```
site:
    @make assets
    @make pages
    @make javadoc
    @make linkcheker
```

Each has it's own make target above that can be run individually as needed. Also, the pip install of linkchecker would be done in `setup`.

